-- Blast at Plastics Plant in Eastern China's Nanjing Kills 6, Xinhua Reports
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-28T07:16:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-28/blast-at-plastics-plant-in-eastern-china-s-nanjing-kills-6-xinhua-reports.html

          
          
             An explosion at an abandoned
plastics and chemical factory in the Chinese city of Nanjing
killed at least six people and injured many others, the Xinhua
News Agency reported today, citing witnesses and hospital staff.  
 A gas leak from a pipeline caused the explosion at about
10:10 a.m. today, the report said. Passengers on a bus passing
the area were among the injured, Xinhua said.  
